(increment and decrement)
the increment opertaor used to increase a variable by 1)
the decrement opertaor used to decrease a variable by 1)
i++(post increment)
++i(pre increment)
i--(post decrement)
--i(pre decrement)
class Oper
{
public static void main(String args[])
{
int a=3;
System.out.println(a);
System.out.println(a++);
System.out.println(--a);
System.out.println(a++);
System.out.println(a);
System.out.println(--a);
System.out.println(a++);
System.out.println(a);
}
}
(conditional opertor or ternary operator)
is an short form of if else statement
variable=(cond)?expression1:expression2;
true means condition 1
false means condition 2
class Oper
{
public static void main(String args[])
{
int a=3;
int b=1;
int c=(a>b)?a:b;
System.out.println(c);
}
}





